			<ns0:name>bbu...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/106710594185928520364/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Nexe loading is not working in Chrome on Windows. The tests fail as well.

I tracked the problem down to the fact that the ppNaClPlugin thinks it gets a Posix file descriptor from the trusted PPB_FileIOTrusted_Dev interface when in fact it gets a Windows File HANDLE. So the problem appears to be in Chrome, in the browser side pepper the PPB_FileIOTrusted_Dev GetOSFileDescriptor function.

The existing code leverages a lot of Chrome code for asynch file download, with lots of security checks, so the simplest fix would involve somehow mapping the windows handle to a Posix file descriptor in the pepper code. I don't know if that's possible. Alternatively, there may be some way to ask Chrome for the file as a Posix file descriptor. Ideas?

